<paragraph id="1854B728FFD7FF8A09868256FCEBFA2D" blockId="3.[151,1059,1086,1431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: 
<taxonomicName id="DFEBCCABFFD7FF8A08E88256FD08FBE9" authority="Zettel, 2021" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[505,761,1086,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aschalewi" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A08E88256FD08FBE9" box="[505,761,1086,1107]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Aphelocheirus aschalewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="31ACD641FFD7FF8A0A108257FCBAFBEE" box="[769,843,1087,1108]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily distinguished from its African congeners by small size and a highly contrasting colour pattern (
<figureCitation id="80D0ABADFFD7FF8A098E8211FF2DFB35" box="[159,220,1145,1167]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[151,184,1390,1412]" captionTargetBox="[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[151,1057,207,1381]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp., habitus of brachypterous male (holotype); legs omitted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038840/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A09E58211FE22FB34" box="[244,467,1145,1166]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Aphelocheirus debilis</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A0B188211FD7CFB34" box="[521,653,1145,1166]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. kumbanus</emphasis>
, both only known in the macropterous female, possess a more strongly produced forehead (see 
<bibRefCitation id="7C7ACAD9FFD7FF8A0BCF82FFFC6DFB16" author="LINNAVUORI R" box="[734,924,1174,1196]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" pagination="89 - 91" refId="ref1976" refString="LINNAVUORI R. (1975): On the genus Aphelochirus (Heteroptera, Naucoridae) of tropical Africa. - Notulae entomologicae 55: 89 - 91." type="journal article" year="1975">LINNAVUORI 1975</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2a, 3a). Experience with Asian species of 
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A08E582DBFD77FB72" box="[500,646,1203,1224]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Aphelocheirus</emphasis>
has shown that the head shape does not vary among wing morphs of the same species. The forewing remnants of 
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A0A9D82B9FBD3FB5C" box="[908,1058,1233,1254]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. schoudeteni</emphasis>
are very small, elongate and widely distant from each other (
<bibRefCitation id="7C7ACAD9FFD7FF8A0A168286FC37FABE" author="LINNAVUORI R" box="[775,966,1262,1284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" pagination="89 - 91" refId="ref1976" refString="LINNAVUORI R. (1975): On the genus Aphelochirus (Heteroptera, Naucoridae) of tropical Africa. - Notulae entomologicae 55: 89 - 91." type="journal article" year="1975">LINNAVUORI 1975</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1a), while those of 
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A08238364FE69FA9A" box="[306,408,1291,1313]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. corbeti</emphasis>
meet each other at body midline (
<bibRefCitation id="7C7ACAD9FFD7FF8A0BEF8363FC65FA9B" author="POISSON R" box="[766,916,1291,1313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" pagination="154 - 170" refId="ref2038" refString="POISSON R. (1955): Sur quelques Hemipteres aquatiques de l'Afrique orientale et descriptions d'especes nouvelles. - Annali del Museo civico di storia naturale Giacomo Doria 68: 154 - 170." type="journal article" year="1955">POISSON 1955</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 13). The size of the forewings is intermediate in 
<taxonomicName id="DFEBCCABFFD7FF8A0B348341FD57FA84" authority="Zettel, 2021" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[549,678,1321,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aschalewi" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A0B348341FD57FA84" box="[549,678,1321,1342]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. aschalewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="31ACD641FFD7FF8A0BBD8341FD07FA84" box="[684,758,1321,1342]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="DFEBCCABFFD7FF8A0AB08341FBD3FA84" authority="Zettel, 2021" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[929,1058,1321,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aschalewi" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A0AB08341FBD3FA84" box="[929,1058,1321,1342]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. aschalewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="31ACD641FFD7FF8A0986832FFF12FAE6" box="[151,227,1351,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, most of all the parameres, resemble those of 
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A0BAF832EFCD5FAE1" box="[702,804,1350,1371]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. corbeti</emphasis>
, suggesting a close relationship, however, the apices of both parameres are broader in 
<taxonomicName id="DFEBCCABFFD7FF8A0A0C830CFC6EFAC2" authority="Zettel, 2021" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2021" box="[797,927,1379,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aschalewi" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A0A0C830CFC6EFAC2" box="[797,927,1379,1401]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. aschalewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="31ACD641FFD7FF8A0AB7830CFC01FAC3" box="[934,1008,1380,1401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
than in 
<emphasis id="2A9F6B3AFFD7FF8A09A083E9FEE7FA2C" box="[177,278,1409,1430]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">A. corbeti</emphasis>
(comp. 
<figureCitation id="80D0ABADFFD7FF8A087883E9FE31FA2C" box="[361,448,1408,1431]" captionStart="Figs 2-8" captionStartId="3.[151,191,967,989]" captionTargetBox="[156,1059,371,939]" captionTargetId="figure-340@3.[154,1065,369,942]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 2-8: Aphelocheirus aschalewi nov.sp.: (2) mesosternum, lateral view; (3) apex of propleuron, ventral view; (4) parandria and aedeagus, dorsal view; (5, 6) right paramere in dorsal (5) and approximately ventral view (6); (7, 8) left paramere in dorsal (7) and ventral view (8)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5038848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5038848/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">Figs 5–8</figureCitation>
with 
<bibRefCitation id="7C7ACAD9FFD7FF8A08EA83E9FD7CFA2C" author="POISSON R" box="[507,653,1408,1430]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142" pagination="154 - 170" refId="ref2038" refString="POISSON R. (1955): Sur quelques Hemipteres aquatiques de l'Afrique orientale et descriptions d'especes nouvelles. - Annali del Museo civico di storia naturale Giacomo Doria 68: 154 - 170." type="journal article" year="1955">POISSON 1955</bibRefCitation>
: figs 13B, C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1854B728FFD7FF8A098683CFFD2EFA63" blockId="3.[151,1058,1446,1497]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1142">E t y m o l o g y: The species name honours Aschalew Haile Lakew for his important role in establishing and conducting the LARIMA Project.</paragraph>
